translation:
In the event of a wound to the mind, soothing and joyful words are well-known;
Similarly, for the young, wholesome amusements and love affairs are beneficial.
Delightful scents, pleasing to the mind, are derived from earth, flowers, fruits, and sour foods;
Prepared vegetables, palatable drinks, six tastes, and edible aromatic substances;
Meats, grains, and various dishes, as well as fragrant, colorful, and tasty fruits and roots, are all successful.

Drink a measure of clarified butter mixed with the powders of vidanga, naga, arista, pippalii, hingu, saundhavan, bhargi, ksarashca, and cured in two kshara (alkalis), five kola (types of plant juices), five salts, and in a cloth that has been washed with the decoction of shatipalaka, nirgundi, danti, musta, and kantakari;

Or apply to the chest liniments made from durable drumstick, grape, clear crystal sugar, liquorice, and vata-expelling oils in cases of cough and vata disorder;

Or lick powders of vidanga, saundhavan, kusta, vyosha, hingu, manahshila, mixed with honey and ghee for relief in cough, hiccups, and asthma.

Golden mountain, mountain with milk-like water, having peaks that are like teeth, and producing fruits and roots; Jati, Pravala, Sarshapa, Lashuna, Vidanga, Karanja, Twak, fruits of Nimba, Citraka, and Kasha;

Kustha, Patha, Mushtha, Tumburu, Murva, Avaca, with six joints; Edaga, Gaja, Kuṭaja, Shigru, Trini, Yooshana, Bhallataka, Kshavaka fruits;

Haritaki, Aak, Pushpika, Tuttha, Kampa, Illaka, named Amritasanje; Sarja, Kaasi, Darvi, Tvak, leaves of Karaveera - with these, oil is prepared. Alternatively, Sarshapa (mustard) oil, or cow's urine, multiplied by four, can also be used [111-115].

Among these senses, the one whose affliction caused by poison, etc., is the greatest;
For some, the suffering is similar in the case of desires and fevers,
The distinguishing feature of fever-like afflictions arising from desires, etc., is stated as follows.
